winning_structure.name: UBX-SEC-OSNMA
winning_structure.description: Galileo Open Service Navigation Message Authentication (OSNMA) security information

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x03 for this version)

fields.name: nmaHeader
fields.description: NMA header (status of the OSNMA service: NMA status, chain in force and CPKS)

bits.name: headerAuthStatus
bits.description: Indicates if the NMA header has been authenticated.

bits.name: nmaStatus
bits.description:
Status of OSNMA service (as indicated by the Galileo system)
0: Service status not authenticated yet
1: OSNMA service in test
2: OSNMA service operational
3: OSNMA service invalid, service not usable

bits.name: chainInForce
bits.description: Id of the TESLA chain in force

bits.name: CPKS
bits.description:
TESLA chain and public key status
0: Data is not applicable
1: Nominal
2: End of Chain (EOC), new DSM-KROOT is being transmitted
3: Chain revoked (CREV), a chain is or has been revoked

fields.name: osnmaMonitoring
fields.description: Monitoring information on OSNMA service as observed by the receiver

bits.name: osnmaEnabled
bits.description: Flag that indicates whether OSNMA execution is enabled in the receiver

bits.name: numberSVs
bits.description: Number of SVs from which OSNMA data is being collected

bits.name: nmaHeaderUpdate
bits.description:
New unauthenticated NMA header (NMA status, chain in force and CPKS) observed in the signal. Changes are pending on authentication. The authentication of the MAC and TESLA keys is discontinued until the new header has been authenticated
0: Last observed NMA header is the same as the last authenticated header
1: New observed NMA header pending on authentication: Update still indicates a healthy service
2: New observed NMA header pending on authentication: Update indicates a problem in the service provision

bits.name: noData
bits.description: If true, OSNMA data is not available for the time defined in CFG-SEC-SPOOFDET_OSNMA_DENIAL_TIME.

bits.name: wrongData
bits.description: If true, OSNMA data is inconsistent.

bits.name: wrongFlxMac
bits.description: If true, flexible slots authentication have failed (FLX)

bits.name: wrongMaclt
bits.description: If true, the tags sequence do not follow the MAC look-up table (MACLT).

fields.name: timSyncReq
fields.description: Information related to OSNMA Time Synchronization requirement status

bits.name: timSyncEnabled
bits.description: Flag that indicates if OSNMA must be executed applying the Time Synchronization requirement

bits.name: timSyncStatus
bits.description:
Indicates if the time synchronization check has been applied.
0: Time synchronization is not performed. Default to outside authentication epochs or when time synchronization is not requested
1: Time synchronization could not be performed, trusted time is not available
2: Time synchronization could not be performed, the trusted time is not accurate enough

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: timSyncReqDiff
fields.description: Time difference from the Time Synchronization requirement. The time difference between the trusted input time and the decoded GSTpropagated to the current local time from the subframe that contains the TESLA key to be authenticated. Note that the time synchronization status must pass or fail (timSyncReq = 3/4). Otherwise, the the time difference cannot be computed

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: dsmAuthentication
fields.description: Information related to the DSM authentication

bits.name: dsmAuthenticationStatus
bits.description:
Indicates if the authentication of a Digital Signature Message has been performed
0: No DSM authentication
1: DSM-KROOT authenticated, new status and configuration accepted
2: DSM-PKR authenticated, new public key accepted
3: OSNMA Alert message: All cryptographic data is dropped. Connect to GSC OSNMA server
4: DSM-KROOT authentication failed, new status and configuration is not accepted
5: DSM-PKR authentication failed, new public key is not accepted
6: Authentication not performed: DSM coded with unknown public key
7: Authentication not performed: Public key decompression failed
8: Authentication successful but new configuration is not supported
9: Authentication of a new public key during a NMT event cannot be performed. Missing future Merkle tree root

bits.name: hashFunction
bits.description: Last authenticated hash function that must be used

bits.name: macFunction
bits.description: Last authenticated MAC function that must be used

bits.name: pubKeyId
bits.description: Last authenticated public key Id that must be used in ECDSA verification

bits.name: macLookupTable
bits.description: Last authenticated MAC Lookup table index

bits.name: keySize
bits.description: Last authenticated TESLA key size index

bits.name: macSize
bits.description: Last authenticated MAC size index. Add an offset of 5 to obtain the index as per Table 11 of OSNMA SIS ICD, Issue 1.1

bits.name: fromNVS
bits.description: Last authenticated configuration comes from NVS

fields.name: teslaKey
fields.description: Information related to the TESLA key authentication

bits.name: teslaKeyAuthStatus
bits.description:
Indicates if the authentication of an element of the TESLA key has been performed and the result thereof
0: No TESLA key authentication performed
1: TESLA key successfully authenticated against the root key
2: TESLA key authentication against the root key has failed
3: TESLA key authentication on-going: Intermediate authentication step
4: TESLA key authentication is not performed: Key to authenticate is in the past. Potential replayed signals or simulation.
5: TESLA key authentication is not performed: The root key is too old

bits.name: wnSf
bits.description: The GST week number of subframe in which the public key has been transmitted

bits.name: towSf
bits.description: Seconds of week of the GST of the subframe in which the public key has been transmitted divided by 30s (subframe length)

bits.name: chainId
bits.description: Chain Id of the TESLA key that has been authenticated

fields.name: generalAndTiming
fields.description: Information related to the overall authentication process: Timing parameters and summary of data authenticated

bits.name: authSVs
bits.description: Total number of SVs for which orbit/clocks data authentication has been performed (ADKD types 0 or 12)

bits.name: authNumTim
bits.description: Total number of timing parameters authentications (typically one per SV sending MAC ADKD type 4)

bits.name: timingAuthResult
bits.description:
Indicates if the authentication of the timing parameters (GST-UTC and GST-GPS) has been performed and the result
0: No timing parameters authentication performed
1: Timing parameters successfully authenticated
2: Timing parameters authentication failed

bits.name: macAdkdType
bits.description:
Indicates if the receiver processes fast (1 subframe delay) or slow (10 subframes delay) MACs
0: Fast MACs (ADKD type 0)
1: Slow MACs (ADKD type 12)

bits.name: pubKeySrc
bits.description:
Origin of the public key
0: Factory default
1: From satellites
2: From aided message
3: From NVS

bits.name: merkleRootSrc
bits.description: Origin of the Merkle tree root

bits.name: merkleRootVal
bits.description:
Validity of the Merkle tree root currently applicable
0: Merkle tree root is invalid
1: Merkle tree root is valid

bits.name: futureMerkleRootSrc
bits.description:
Origin of the future Merkle tree root
0: Factory default
2: From aided message
3: From NVS

bits.name: futureMerkleRootVal
bits.description:
Validity of the future Merkle tree root
0: Future Merkle tree root is invalid or unknown
1: Future Merkle tree root is valid

bits.name: pubKeyVal
bits.description:
Validity of the public key
0: Public key is invalid or unknown
1: Public key is valid

bits.name: futurePubKeyVal
bits.description:
Validity of the future public key
0: Future public key is invalid or unknown
1: Future public key is valid

bits.name: futurePubKeySrc
bits.description:
Origin of the future public key
0: Factory default
1: From satellites
3: From NVS

bits.name: futurePubKeyId
bits.description: Last authenticated public key Id that will be used in ECDSA verification after the next key update

fields.name: bitfield1
fields.description: bitfield:

bits.name: IODE
bits.description: Issue of data, authenticated ephemeris

bits.name: authNum
bits.description: Number of times that the same block of navigation data has been authenticated in last execution

bits.name: authStatus
bits.description:
Indicates the authentication result for current SV's orbits, clocks, flags, group delays and ionospheric delay data:
0: Navigation data authentication failed
1: Navigation data successfully authenticated

fields.name: svId
fields.description: Satellite identifier whose data gets authenticated (see Satellite Numbering)

fields.name: reserved2
fields.description: Reserved

structure.description: Galileo Open Service Navigation Message Authentication (OSNMA) security information. Information related to the execution of OSNMA protocol. Reports periodically the total number of satellites transmitting OSNMA data, the latest authenticated service status and configuration and the authentication results per satellite.

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x03 for this version)

fields.name: nmaHeader
fields.description:
NMA header (status of the OSNMA service: NMA status, chain in force and CPKS).
Bit 0 (U:1): 'headerAuth' - Indicates if the NMA header has been authenticated.
Bits 2-1 (U:2): 'nmaStatus' - Status of OSNMA service (0: Not authenticated yet, 1: In test, 2: Operational, 3: Invalid).
Bits 4-3 (U:2): 'chainInForce' - ID of the TESLA chain in force.
Bits 7-5 (U:3): 'CPKS' - TESLA chain and public key status (0: Data not applicable, 1: Nominal, 2: End of Chain (EOC), 3: Chain revoked (CREV), 4: New public key (NPK), 5: Public key revocation (PKREV), 6: New Merkle tree (NMT), 7: Alert message (AM)).

fields.name: osnmaMonitoring
fields.description:
Monitoring information on OSNMA service as observed by the receiver.
Bit 0 (U:1): 'osnmaEnabled' - Flag that indicates whether OSNMA execution is enabled.
Bits 5-1 (U:5): 'numberSVs' - Number of SVs from which OSNMA data is being collected.
Bits 7-6 (U:2): 'nmaHeaderUpdate' - New unauthenticated NMA header (0: Last observed NMA header is the same, 1: New header pending authentication, healthy service, 2: New header pending authentication, problem in service provision).
Bit 8 (U:1): 'noData' - If true, OSNMA data is not available.
Bit 9 (U:1): 'wrongData' - If true, OSNMA data is inconsistent.
Bit 10 (U:1): 'wrongFlxMac' - If true, flexible slots authentication have failed (FLX).
Bit 11 (U:1): 'wrongMaclt' - If true, the tags sequence do not follow the MAC look-up table (MACLT).

fields.name: timSyncReq
fields.description:
Information related to OSNMA Time Synchronization requirement status.
Bit 0 (U:1): 'timSyncEnabled' - Flag that indicates if OSNMA must be executed applying the Time Synchronization requirement.
Bits 3-1 (U:3): 'timSyncStatus' - Indicates if the time synchronization check has been applied (0: Not performed, 1: Could not be performed - no trusted time, 2: Could not be performed - trusted time not accurate, 3: Check passed, 4: Check failed - replay attack).

fields.name: timSyncReqDiff
fields.description: Time difference from the Time Synchronization requirement.

fields.name: dsmAuthentication
fields.description:
Information related to the DSM authentication.
Bits 5-0 (U:6): 'dsmAuthenticationStatus' (0: No DSM authentication, 1: DSM-KROOT authenticated, 2: DSM-PKR authenticated, 3: OSNMA Alert message, 4: DSM-KROOT authentication failed, 5: DSM-PKR authentication failed, 6: Authentication not performed: Unknown public key, 7: Authentication not performed: Public key decompression failed, 8: Authentication successful but new configuration is not supported, 9: Authentication of a new public key during NMT event, missing future Merkle tree root).
Bits 7-6 (U:2): 'hashFunction' - Last authenticated hash function that must be used.
Bits 9-8 (U:2): 'macFunction' - Last authenticated MAC function that must be used.
Bits 13-10 (U:4): 'pubKeyId' - Last authenticated public key ID for ECDSA verification.
Bits 21-14 (U:8): 'macLookupTable' - Last authenticated MAC Lookup table index.
Bits 25-22 (U:4): 'keySize' - Last authenticated TESLA key size index.
Bits 29-26 (U:4): 'macSize' - Last authenticated MAC size index. Add offset of 5 for OSNMA SIS ICD, Issue 1.1.
Bit 30 (U:1): 'fromNVS' - Last authenticated configuration comes from NVS.

fields.name: teslaKey
fields.description:
Information related to the TESLA key authentication.
Bits 2-0 (U:3): 'teslaKeyAuthStatus' (0: No TESLA key authentication, 1: Success against root key, 2: Failed against root key, 3: On-going, 4: Not performed - key in past, 5: Not performed - root key too old).
Bits 14-3 (U:12): 'wnSf' - GST week number of subframe with public key.
Bits 29-15 (U:15): 'towSf' - Seconds of week of GST of subframe (divided by 30s).
Bits 31-30 (U:2): 'chainId' - Chain ID of the TESLA key.

fields.name: authSVs
fields.description: Total number of SVs for which orbit/clocks data authentication has been performed (ADKD types 0 or 12). This field corresponds to bits 5-0 of the original X4 field 'generalAndTiming'.

fields.name: generalAndTiming_reserved
fields.description: Remaining part of the original X4 'generalAndTiming' field.

fields.name: bitfield1
fields.description:
Bitfield: Issue of data, authenticated ephemeris.
Bits 9-0 (U:10): 'IODE' - Issue of data, authenticated ephemeris.
Bits 14-10 (U:5): 'authNum' - Number of times same block of navigation data authenticated.
Bit 15 (U:1): 'authStatus' - Authentication result for current SV's data (0: Failed, 1: Successful).

fields.name: svId
fields.description: Satellite identifier whose data gets authenticated (see Satellite Numbering).
